records.label: Cancer Sharing Limits
records.userValues: The Lifetime Limit for all Cancer is $500,000; each Incident cannot exceed the Maximum Limit Per Incident.

records.label: For Members who have never been diagnosed/received treatment for any Cancer
records.userValues: Sharing is eligible after a 90 day waiting period from the Member's effective date. If Cancer is diagnosed within the 90 day waiting period, the diagnosis/treatment expenses related to that Cancer, recurrence or metastasis are not eligible for sharing.

records.label: Need for member diagnosed/treated for cancer more than 5 yrs. prior to eff date
records.userValues: Medical records must show member was Cancer free 5 years immediately prior to the effective date, indicating no ongoing treatment or future treatment was prescribed/planned and the member has followed Cancer screening and healthy lifestyle guidelines.

records.label: Limitations for members diagnosed/treated for cancer within 5 yrs. of eff date
records.userValues: If a Member was diagnosed, or treatment was received, for Cancer within 5 years of the Member effective date, Cancer expenses are Not Eligible for Sharing

records.label: Limitation for member diagnosed/treated for cancer more than 5 yr. of eff date
records.userValues: If a Member was diagnosed, or treatment was received, for Cancer more than 5 years prior to the Member effective date, expenses for a newly diagnosed Cancer may be eligible for sharing, after a 90 day waiting period.

records.label: Pre-Existing or Recurrent
records.userValues: Cancer Expenses are not eligible for sharing.

records.label: Cancer Look Back Period
records.userValues: If a Member was diagnosed, or treatment was received, for Cancer within 5 years of the Member effective date, Cancer expenses are Not Eligible for Sharing.
